choices.text:
, will there be enough food
for me to eat? For these street children and boys rescued from human trafficking, it is an awful reality. I have seen them wanting and starving. Their two worst enemies are troubled minds and empty stomachs. One day I gave them food I had bought for myself back in Cambodia.
It was too small and insufficient for me, but everyone ate and smiled. They were so, so happy to receive it.
But I tell them that God, the Creator and Giver of all, can bring more than enough to His children.
At that particular time, something miraculous happened. Newspapers said I had won one of the three top awards from Voice of America’s Best Emerging Blogger Award 2011. The other top bloggers are very famous in their own countries.
Payments came via Western Union from the U.S. and the door for greater ministry opportunities opened before me.
Today, thanks to a small handful of committed volunteers and believers in Cambodia, we are building a two-and-a-half story Children and Youth Center in Phnom Penh to help children, especially girls at risk, who have no home or are living on the streets. It gives us great joy to see the dedication, the capacity and satisfaction in the volunteers and the children. My biggest desire is to have more Christian believers join us in this work as overseers and teachers for these at-risk children and youths.
